8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 17, L.D. 53, “An Act to Establish the
10 November General Election Day as a State Holiday”
11 Amend the bill by striking out the title and substituting the following:
12 'An Act to Establish the November General Election Day as a School Holiday
13 Applicable Only to Public School Buildings Used as Voting Places'
14 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the enacting clause and inserting the
15 following:
16 'Sec. 1. 20-A MRSA §4801, sub-§1, ¶G is enacted to read:
17 G. Notwithstanding any provision of law to the contrary, with respect to a school
18 building closed on the day of the general election pursuant to section 4802, subsection
19 1, paragraph E-1, the school administrative unit is not required to add an additional
20 instruction day for that affected school even if the closure results in the affected school
21 not meeting the number of instructional days required by this section.
22 Sec. 2. 20-A MRSA §4801, sub-§1, ¶H is enacted to read:
23 H. Notwithstanding any provision of law to the contrary, with respect to a school
24 building closed on the day of the general election pursuant to section 4802, subsection
25 1, paragraph E-1, if the school administrative unit schedules in place of an instructional
26 day an in-service day for the education of teachers, administrative meetings, parent-
27 teacher conferences, records' days or similar activities as described in this section, the
28 school administrative unit is not required to reduce the number of in-service days for
29 the affected school even if the in-service day results in the affected school exceeding
30 the number of in-service days permitted by this section.
31 Sec. 3. 20-A MRSA §4802, sub-§1, ¶E-1 is enacted to read:
32 E-1. The day of the general election, as defined in Title 21-A, section 1, subsection
33 19, applicable only to a school building within a school administrative unit that will be
34 used as a voting place for that election, except that the school administrative unit is not
35 required to close that building if:
