1 (1) The school administrative unit provides for the remote instruction, as defined
2 in section 6804-A, of students that attend that building; or
3 (2) The school administrative unit schedules in place of an instructional day an in-
4 service day for the education of teachers, administrative meetings, parent-teacher
5 conferences, records' days or similar activities pursuant to section 4801, subsection
6 1.
7 As used in this paragraph, "voting place" has the same meaning as in Title 21-A, section
8 1, subsection 49;'
9 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
10 number to read consecutively.
11 SUMMARY
1122 This amendment, which is the majority report of the committee, replaces the bill and
1133 changes the title. The amendment establishes the day of the general election, as defined in
1144 the Maine Revised Statutes, Title 21-A, section 1, subsection 19, as a school holiday
1155 applicable only to a school building within a school administrative unit that will be used as
1166 a voting place for that election, except that the school administrative unit is not required to
1177 close that building if the school administrative unit provides for the remote instruction, as
1188 defined in Title 20-A, section 6804-A, of students that attend that building or if the school
1199 administrative unit decides to schedule in place of an instructional day an in-service day
2200 for the education of teachers, administrative meetings, parent-teacher conferences, records'
2211 days or similar activities pursuant to Title 20-A, section 4801, subsection 1.
22 The amendment also provides that, notwithstanding any provision of law to the
23 contrary, with respect to a school building closed on the day of the general election pursuant
24 to Title 20-A, section 4802, subsection 1, paragraph E-1, the school administrative unit is
25 not required to add an additional instructional day for that affected school even if the
26 closure results in the affected school not meeting the number of instructional days required
27 by Title 20-A, section 4801, subsection 1.
28 It also provides that, notwithstanding any provision of law to the contrary, with respect
29 to a school building closed on the day of the general election pursuant to Title 20-A, section
30 4802, subsection 1, paragraph E-1, if the school administrative unit decides to schedule in
31 place of an instructional day an in-service day for the education of teachers, administrative
32 meetings, parent-teacher conferences, records' days or similar activities as described in
33 Title 20-A, section 4801, subsection 1, the school administrative unit is not required to
34 reduce the number of in-service days for the affected school even if the in-service day
35 results in the affected school exceeding the number of in-service days permitted by Title
36 20-A, section 4801, subsection 1.
